CRYPTOHACK Challenge: Great Snakes
Points: 3
Category: Cryptography / Python Basics
Platform: CryptoHack

Modern cryptography involves code, and code involves coding. CryptoHack provides a good opportunity to sharpen your skills. 
Of all modern programming languages, Python 3 stands out as ideal for quickly writing cryptographic scripts and attacks. 
Run the attached Python script and it will output your flag.

Input:

#!/usr/bin/env python3

import sys
# import this

if sys.version_info.major == 2:
    print("You are running Python 2, which is no longer supported. Please update to Python 3.")

ords = [81, 64, 75, 66, 70, 93, 73, 72, 1, 92, 109, 2, 84, 109, 66, 75, 70, 90, 2, 92, 79]

print("Here is your flag:")
print("".join(chr(o ^ 0x32) for o in ords))  
//with XOR Operation
//The function chr() converts the resulting number into its corresponding ASCII character.
//The "".join() function combines all characters together into a single string, revealing the flag.

